mythischen Gehalten umzugehen  aThe volume presents papers on the subject of "Myths in the Middle Ages", and harnesses the theoretical discussions on the concept of myth for German medieval studies. It is divided into three sections, which stand for various methodological approaches: I. Myth and Christianity, II. Myth and Narrative, III. Myth and Presence. The outcome is that the Middle Ages developed (narrative) strategies on different levels for dealing with mythical material.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 4aMittelalter /Geistes- und Kulturleben. 4aMittelalter /Literatur. 4aMythologie /i.d.Literatur. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh1 aBürkle, Susanne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFriedrich, Udo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFriedrich, Udo, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGumbrecht, Hans Ulrich, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHaferland, Harald, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHuber, Christoph, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKellner, Beate, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKiening, Christian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKöbele, Susanne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLinder, Andreas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMartínez, Matías, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMüller, Jan-Dirk, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPetersen, Christoph, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aQuast, Bruno, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.lo